Grohmann, Egyptian Library, I, pp. 25–31, III, pp. 11–43, 47–55; C. H. Becker, Papyri Schott-Reinhardt, I, Veröffentlichungen aus der Heidelberger Papyrus-Sammlung, III, Heidelberg, 1906 (all the papyri in this volume are Qurrah's); the same author's "Arabische Papyri des Aphroditofundes," in Zeitschrift für Assyriologie, XX, 1907, pp. 68–104, and "Neue arabische Papyri des Aphroditofundes," in Der Islam, II, 1911, pp. 245–268; Nabia Abbott, The Kurrah Papyri from Aphrodito in the Oriental Institute (The Oriental Institute Studies in Ancient Oriental Civilization, No. 15, Chicago, 1938), where, in addition to Qurrah documents, there is a biography of the Governor (pp. 57–69); H. Lammens, Études sur le Siècle des Omayyades, Beyrouth, 1930, pp. 305–323. The alleged scandal of Qurrah's drinking bouts in the mosque of 'Amr as a means of disposing of treasury surpluses, doubtless a fabrication of the Governor's 'Abbāsid maligners, is recounted in Lane-Poole, History, p. 26.

